Geographic origin: Vincennes, Knox County, Indiana, United States
Notes on original: Collected 06/29; sprayed with sterilac (alkaline chloramine); 1 gram in 70 cc water. One application a few days before collection. Plat 32 of experiment in Cushing Orchard at Vincennes, Indiana, 1923. See notes. Defoliation very heavy. Leaves fell with little visible injury. Substance seems to leave peculiar effect on abscess layer.
Name: Prunus persica
